    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    5 Stars
    Ticks all the boxes.
    A fantastic smartphone that offers a great balance of speed, efficiency, and battery life - however, the battery with its small capacity is definitely the weakest point of this phone. It has a gorgeous 6.2-inch display, a powerful Tensor G3 chip and a camera that consistently takes stunning photos - It may not have a fancy lenses from Leica but the software behind the photo processing is incredible and the results are fantastic. The 8 is also incredibly secure, with a robust security system that will keep your personal data safe. I'm confident that my information is well-protected when I'm using this phone. I have switched from Xiaomi 13 and the switch itself was a breeze - initially its doable over the wifi, but the content transfer (photos, videos, etc) been done via the usb-c cable, as you can see at the attached photo. I've noticed, the phone gets a mixed reviews but it may come from the fact, that people don't know how to use all the features. Personally I think it one of the best phones currently available, may compete with the flagships but costs a fraction.The only downsides are the smaller battery and slower charging speed, but these are minor issues compared to the Pixel 8's overall 'awesomeness'. If you're looking for an android smartphone that doesn't mess around, the Google Pixel 8 is the way to go.

    5.0 out of 5 stars Great everyday phone
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 25 December 2023
    Colour: HazelSize Name: 128GBStyle Name: Pixel 8Verified Purchase
    Honestly this is a great buy, its camera is fantastic, as is the screen. It's a fairly mid sized phone, so if you're used to larger ones (I had a Galaxy A32 before this, and its notably smaller than even that) it may take a while to get used to typing on the smaller available field.
    My only note is the '24 hour' battery claim. If you're using it a lot during travel, such as bus or rail you'll be lucky to last 10 hours on one charge. If you're not excessively using it or using power hungry apps, you'll probably be fine there though.

    Overall, a great mid-range phone for the price, especially if you don't want to splash out extra for the Pro version.

    JPS
    3.0 out of 5 stars Disappointing
    Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 2 April 2024
    Colour: HazelSize Name: 128GBStyle Name: Pixel 8Verified Purchase
    I wanted to love this phone. Having tried Apple, Samsung & various others over the years, the reviews for the Pixel 8 prompted me to give this phone a try.
    That was a mistake overall. Compared to the market leaders, this phone feels cheap and plastic. The user interface is clunky, for example swiping across to see open apps can take 3 or 4 attempts. Trying to change the photo settings on the camera is highly frustrating and not at all intuitive.
    As a work phone, the Google maps was important to me but the interface with my car is sketchy, dropping Bluetooth regularly and strange pop ups appear randomly on the screen. Not what I expected from a Google phone.
    The shape of the phone with the proud camera section on the rear makes it odd to place on a surface and damage to the lens section is a worry.
    Charging the unit takes a long time and battery life is nowhere near as good as my old Galaxy S8 from years ago.
    The energy saving mode seems to darken the screen so much you need to squint to focus. So that mode is pointless.
    There are positives. It has a decent camera for the price, the water resistance is good and processing power has been fine.
    However, I would go back to Samsung next time and pay a little more for a premium product that is easier to use and feels well built. A disappointing purchase overall.
    UPDATE: with Bluetooth dropping out in car, I have since learned that this is a known product problem (Google support website comments). As this is crucial to my business (along with call drops), I am returning the unit.

    Provengo dal un Asus Zenfone 8, ancora oggi con caratteristiche tecniche al top, ma con schermo haim rotto. Ho voluto cambiare principalmente per la fotografia, perch non era di qualit. Eccomi qui da un giorno con questo Pixel 8, da cui scrivo. Prima di tutto le note negative. Leggero, ma pi pesante del precedente Asus e la cosa che mi piace meno il materiale del retro, bello, colorato, ma scivolosissimo, non si riesce a tenere in mano, assolutamente necessaria una custodia di gomma che faccia grip, e poi il peso maggiore sulla parte alta nel comparto fotografico, rendendo pericoloso maneggiarlo, senza cover. Ora passiamo al resto. Schermo veramente definito e si nota la differenza con il mio precedente telefono, ci leggo meglio le scritte pi piccole, inoltre senza bordi rendendo la grandezza del display maggiore. Velocit delle app decisamente buona e fluida. Fotografia, senza usare l'intelligenza artificiale, di buon qualit, con foto non distorte, dettagliate e poi la macro reale senza sfocature o distorsioni di immagine. Il riconoscimento volto ottimo in ambiente luminoso e decisamente ottimo il riconoscimento impronte sotto il display, funziona sempre al primo colpo. Sono mi sembra di qualit e forte, seppure stiamo parlando di un telefono e non di un impianto HiFi. Lo trovo anche pi veloce in navigazione internet e comunque in connessione wifi rispetto al telefono precedente. Sul lato software chiaramente Google ha puntato tutto sulla sua intelligenza artificiale, ed in fase di primo avvio del telefono chiede quali intelligenze attivare. Su questo aspetto ci sono molte chicche da scoprire. So che un giorno solo di test non sufficiente per dare un giudizio esaustivo, ma sono un appassionato di tecnologia che ha cambiato decine di telefoni nella vita e ritengo di saper rilevare pregi e difetti in pochi istanti, grazie a questa passione. Non dico nulla sulla durata batteria perch va testata in pi contesti ed usi.
